OL,3,CLoyalist Irvine jailed but 'peace'
OL,4,Cefforts see him escape five-year term
OL,6,FLeading loyalist Winston Irvine has
OL,7,Fbeen jailed for 15months after he was
OL,8,Fcaught with firearms and ammunition in
OL,9,Fthe boot of his car.
OL,11,FIn all Irvine was sentenced to 30
OL,12,Fmonths with half his term to be served
OL,13,Fon licence.
OL,15,FImposing the sentence, Judge Gordon
OL,16,FKerr KC ruled that there were
OL,17,F"exceptional circumstances" in his
OL,18,Fcase, namely Irvine's "work for peace
OL,19,Fand his charity work in the community".
