OL,3,CLoyalist Irvine jailed but 'peace'
OL,4,Cefforts see him escape five-year term
OL,6,FJudge Kerr said he had taken into
OL,7,Faccount the references praising
OL,8,FIrvine's work in the community when
OL,9,Fassessing whether the case involved
OL,10,Fexceptional circumstances.
OL,12,F"I do consider a combination of the
OL,13,Fmatters relating to the defendant do
OL,14,Freach a level which could be described
OL,15,Fas exceptional, in particular the
OL,16,Fdefendant's work for peace and charity
OL,17,Fwork in the community," he said.
OL,19,FHe said it would therefore not be
OL,20,Fproper to impose the statutory five-
OL,21,Fyear sentence.
